                                                  <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 10 items
                                                  (a-j)</head>
                                                  <msContents
                                                  class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089787 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85024485 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109389">
                                                  <summary>Collection of works on Naqshbandī,
                                                  Chishtī, Qādirī, Kubravī, and Suhravardī Sufism,
                                                  hagiography, spiritual genealogy, and
                                                  commemorative poetry. Volume not dated; item c
                                                  dated (23 Rabīʿ al-Avval 1189/24 May 1775), with
                                                  later portions dated as late as 7 Rabīʿ al-Avval
                                                  1207/23 October 1792. Scribal nastaʿlīq and Indian
                                                  taʿlīq by the same hand. According to a note at
                                                  the beginning (lower right, f. 1v) the volume was
                                                  transcribed by the author. Annotations in margins.
                                                  Stamped and Persian foliation. Lacking original
                                                  binding. Binding, red half leather IOL covers,
                                                  stamp dated 27 Sept 1916. Folios rebound, but
                                                  disarranged and reoriented; cropped, wormholes,
                                                  water stains, later repairs; gauze overlay on
                                                  folios from the beginning and end. Condition
                                                  fragile. IOL microfilm 1112. </summary>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic </textLang>
                                                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item1">
                                                  <locus from="2v" to="3v">ff. 2v-3v </locus>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="ar" otherLangs="fa">Arabic and
                                                  Persian </textLang>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 a. </p><p>List of
                                                  contents for item b. </p><p>Not dated at end.
                                                  </p><p>Notes primarily on
                                                  <orgName>Naqshbandī</orgName> Sufi scholars and
                                                  saints (f. 1). </p></note>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22217"
                                                  >Fihrist</title>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22217"
                                                  >فهرست</title>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item2">
                                                  <locus from="4v" to="306r">ff. 4v-306r </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 b. </p><p>Substantial
                                                  fragment from a detailed treatise on
                                                  <orgName>Naqshbandī</orgName> Sufi scholars and
                                                  saints, by <persName key="person_f8085" role="aut"
                                                  >Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah
                                                  Muḥammad Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName> (d.
                                                  1205/1790-1), follower of <persName
                                                  key="person_f8246" role="oth">Ḥāfiẓ ʿAbd al-Ghafūr
                                                  Pishāvarī</persName>, and inspired by the
                                                  <persName key="person_f8247" role="oth">Shaykh
                                                  al-Islām Mullā ʿAbd al-Salām</persName>.
                                                  </p><p>Not dated at end. </p><p>The transcription
                                                  alternates between neat scribal nastaʿlīq and a
                                                  fluent Indian taʿlīq hand. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic</textLang>
                                                  <author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                                  key="person_f8095">Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn Muḥammad
                                                  Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah Muḥammad Ibrāhīm
                                                  al-Kashmīrī</persName><persName xml:lang="fa"
                                                  key="person_f8095">شيخ شرف الدّين محمّد زهگير ابن
                                                  خواجه محمّد براهيم الكشميرى</persName></author>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22218"
                                                  >Rawz̤at al-salām</title>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22218">روضة
                                                  السّلام</title>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item3">
                                                  <locus from="307r" to="492r">ff. 307r-492r </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 c. </p><p>Substantial
                                                  excerpt from a treatise on Sufism identified at
                                                  the beginning as <title key="work_21680">Shavāhid
                                                  al-tajdīd</title>, the authorship of which is not
                                                  indicated. </p><p>Dated colophon crossed out (f.
                                                  492r): completed in the house of <persName
                                                  key="person_f8248" role="oth">Muḥammad Fāz̤il
                                                  jīv</persName>, Wednesday, 23 Rabīʿ al-Avval
                                                  1189/24 May 1775. </p><p>Folio 309 bound inverted.
                                                  </p><p>Diagrams on folios 309, 433, 456, 458, 464.
                                                  </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic</textLang>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21680"
                                                  >Shavāhid al-tajdīd</title>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21680">شواهد
                                                  التّجديد</title>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item4">
                                                  <locus from="492r" to="495r">ff. 492r-495r</locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 d. </p><p>Multiple
                                                  spiritual genealogies of Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn
                                                  Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah Muḥammad Ibrāhīm
                                                  al-Kashmīrī (d. 1205/1790-1) linked to the
                                                  <orgName>Naqshbandī</orgName> and
                                                  <orgName>Qādirī</orgName> orders. </p><p>Not dated
                                                  at end. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic </textLang>
                                                  <note/>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item5">
                                                  <locus from="495r" to="496r">ff. 495r-496r </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 e. </p><p>Certificate
                                                  of the spiritual genealogy of <persName
                                                  key="person_f8085" role="subject">Shaykh Sharaf
                                                  al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah Muḥammad
                                                  Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName> (d. 1205/1790-1)
                                                  linking him to the <orgName>Kubravīyah</orgName>
                                                  Sufi Order, issued 29 Z̲ī Ḥijjah 1176/11 July
                                                  1763. </p><p>Not dated at end. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic</textLang>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22220"
                                                  >Ijāzat'nāmah</title>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22220">اجازت
                                                  نامه</title>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item6">
                                                  <locus from="496v" to="498r">ff. 496v-498r </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 f. </p><p>Untitled
                                                  account combining the spiritual genealogies of
                                                  <persName key="person_f8085" role="subject">Shaykh
                                                  Sharaf al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah
                                                  Muḥammad Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName> (d.
                                                  1205/1790-1) from the perspectives of the
                                                  <orgName>Suhravardīyah</orgName> and
                                                  <orgName>Naqshbandīyah</orgName> Sufi Orders,
                                                  issued in 14 Z̲ī Ḥijjah 1175/6 July 1762 and
                                                  1177/1763-4 respectively. </p><p>Not dated at end.
                                                  </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic</textLang>
                                                  <note/>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item7">
                                                  <locus from="498r" to="499r">ff. 498r-499r </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 g. </p><p>Untitled
                                                  certification of the spiritual genealogy of
                                                  <persName key="person_f8085" role="subject">Shaykh
                                                  Sharaf al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah
                                                  Muḥammad Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName> (d.
                                                  1205/1790-1) linking him to the
                                                  <orgName>Chishtīyah</orgName> Sufi Order, dated 6
                                                  Rajab 1177/10 January 1764. </p><p>Not dated at
                                                  end. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic </textLang>
                                                  <note/>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item8">
                                                  <locus from="499r" to="499v">ff. 499r-499v </locus>
                                                  <author/>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 h. </p><p>Certificate
                                                  of the spiritual genealogy of <persName
                                                  key="person_f8085" role="subject">Shaykh Sharaf
                                                  al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah Muḥammad
                                                  Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName> (d. 1205/1790-1)
                                                  linking him to the <orgName>Qādirīyah</orgName>
                                                  Sufi Order, dated 1196/1782. </p><p>Not dated at
                                                  end. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic </textLang>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22220"
                                                  >Ijāzat'nāmah</title>
                                                  <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22220">اجازت
                                                  نامه</title>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item9">
                                                  <locus from="499v" to="500v">ff. 499v-500v </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 i. </p><p>Fragment of
                                                  an untitled essay explaining the multiple
                                                  spiritual and formal Sufi affiliations of
                                                  <persName key="person_f8085" role="subject">Shaykh
                                                  Sharaf al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah
                                                  Muḥammad Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName> (d.
                                                  1205/1790-1). </p><p>There is a lacuna between
                                                  folios 499-500. </p><p>Defective at end.
                                                  </p><p>Not dated at end. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic</textLang>
                                                  <note/>
                                                  </msItem>
                                                  <msItem n="10"
                                                  xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_650-item10">
                                                  <locus from="501r" to="502r">ff. 501r-502r </locus>
                                                  <note><p>Delhi Persian 650 j.
                                                   </p><p>Miscellaneous collection of verses
                                                  consisting of chronogrammatic qiṭaʿāt and
                                                  ghazalīyāt commemorating the <q>ʿurs</q> or date
                                                  of death of <persName key="person_f8085"
                                                  role="subject">Bābā Ṣāḥib Zih'gīr</persName> or
                                                  rather <persName key="person_f8085" role="subject"
                                                  >Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn Muḥammad Zih'gīr ibn Khvājah
                                                  Muḥammad Ibrāhīm al-Kashmīrī</persName>, yielding
                                                  the date 1205/1790-1. </p><p>This is followed by
                                                  compositions relating to the commemorations of
                                                  <persName key="person_f8249" role="subject"
                                                  >Khvājah Muḥammad Qāsim Ṣāḥib</persName>,
                                                  <persName key="person_f8250" role="subject">Jalāl
                                                  Bābā Kāmrājī</persName>, and <persName
                                                  key="person_f8251" role="subject">Bābā Niʿmat
                                                  Allāh Ṣāḥib Kāmrājī</persName>. </p><p>Not dated
                                                  at end. </p><p>On the proceeding folio (503r) is a
                                                  note by a certain <persName key="person_f8252"
                                                  role="ctb">Muḥammad Akbar</persName>, dated 7
                                                  Rabīʿ al-Avval 1207/23 October 1792. </p></note>
                                                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian
                                                  and Arabic</textLang>
                                                  <note/>
                                                  </msItem>
